                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "C"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "IP address \n\n\n\nAND \n\nSubnetMask\nSubnetid \n\n\n\n M: 100.10.5.00000010 \n\n\n\nAND \n\n\n255.255.255.11111100 \n\nSID = 100.10.5.0  \n\nN : 100.10.5.00000101 \n\n\n\nAND \n\n\n255.255.255.11111100 \n\nSID = 100.10.5.00000100 \n\nSID = 100.10.5.4 \n\n\nP : 100.10.5.00000110 \n\n\n\nAND \n\n\n255.255.255.11111100 \n\nSID = 100.10.5.00000100 \n\n\n    100.10.5.4  \n\n\nN & P belong to same subnet. So, option c is the \nanswer.",
