            "question": {
                "text": "If a class B network on the Internet has a subnet mask \nof 255.255.248.0, what is the maximum number of \nhosts per subnet?",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "1022",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "1023",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "2046",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "2047 \nClassless Addressing",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "C"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "Given,  \n\nSubnet Mask: 255.255.248.0  \n\nSM : 11111111.11111111.11111000.00000000 \nHID = 11 bit \n\nMaximum number of Hosts/Subnet  = 211 - 2 \n\n\n\n\n\n= 2048 - 2  \n\n\n\n\n\n= 2046 \n\nSo, option C is the correct answer.",
